The paper proposes an algorithm for learning the Horn envelope of an arbitrary domain using an expert capable of answering certain types of queries about the domain. This involves concepts from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), which suggests that cs.AI and cs.LG are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions formal concept analysis, which is a branch of discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science, indicating that cs.DS and cs.DM are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses a polynomial-time algorithm, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, suggesting that cs.CC is a possible sub-category as well.
